The paper focuses on developing a decentralized visual SLAM system for multi-robot applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system heavily relies on computer vision techniques, such as image descriptors and data association, which suggests a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV) as well. The paper also mentions the use of optimization methods for pose-graph optimization, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) or machine learning (cs.MA, cs.LG) depending on the specific techniques used.
